.TH simple_shell 1 "April 2025" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a basic shell written in C as part of the Holberton School curriculum.  
It supports interactive and non-interactive modes, and allows users to run basic UNIX commands using full paths.

This version supports only single-word commands with no arguments.  
It does not handle pipes, redirections, or environment path search.

.SH USAGE
To start the shell, compile the source code and run:

.B ./hsh

Once inside the shell, type a full path to a command and press ENTER:

.EX
#cisfun$ /bin/ls

To exit, use Ctrl+D (EOF).

To run in non-interactive mode:

.B echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh

